        <profileDesc>
            <creation/>
            <abstract>
                <p>This short treatise describes the positions of moonrise and moonset in the six 'gates'. The text lists the numbers of days for which the moon rises or sets in each 'gate' (as identified in <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/ACFXC8CA"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Neugebauer1979Astronomy"/><title level="m">Ethiopic Astronomy and Computus</title><title level="s">Österreichische Akademie der Wissenschaften, philosophisch-historische Klasse, Sitzungsberichte</title><author><forename>Otto</forename><surname>Neugebauer</surname></author><pubPlace>Wien</pubPlace><publisher>Verlag der Österreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften</publisher><date>1979</date><series><title level="s">Österreichische Akademie der Wissenschaften, philosophisch-historische Klasse, Sitzungsberichte</title><biblScope unit="volume">347, Veröffentlichungen der Kommission für Geschichte der Mathematik, Naturwissenschaften und Medizin, 22</biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">347, Veröffentlichungen der Kommission für Geschichte der Mathematik, Naturwissenschaften und Medizin, 22</biblScope><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:Neugebauer1979Astronomy</note></note><note type="tag">bm:Neugebauer1979Astronomy</note><citedRange unit="page">159</citedRange></bibl>). The list is provided for the twelve Ethiopian months (with the exception of <foreign xml:lang="gez">Ṗāgʷǝmen</foreign>), 
                    starting with <foreign xml:lang="gez">Miyāzyā</foreign> and the fourth 'gate'. The arrangement of the 'gates' and months follows that of the gates-type diagrams. The text is related to the concepts transmitted in 
                    <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1340EnochE#Luminaries"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT1340EnochE#Luminaries</span></ref>. 
                    Note that <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BAVet119">Vatican City, Biblioteca Apostolica Vaticana, Aeth.119</ref> has an addition <foreign xml:lang="gez">ከመዝ፡ ይሠርቁ፡ በሠርቀ፡ ዕብራውያን፡ ወበወርኃ፡ ዕብራውያን።</foreign> at the 
                    beginning of the text.</p>
            </abstract>
